data.title: King Wenceslaus II of Bohemia (1271
data.meta_description: Royalty. King of Bohemia and Poland. He was the only surviving son of Přemysl Ottokar II and Kunigunde von Halicz.  ∼Wenceslaus II  was King of Bohemia, Duke of Cracow and King of Poland. He was the only son of King Ottokar II of Bohemia and Ottokar's second wife Kunigunda. He was born in 1271, ten years after the...
